{"TopicId":204215,"ForumId":18,"TopicTitle":"A new puzzle...","CreatedByName":"GoSlash27","CreatedById":111526,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-05T15:39:57Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"GoSlash27","CreatedById":111526,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-05T15:39:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne of my engineers has an equation on his white board\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E6\u002B4\u002B3=2\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHe insists that it is a correct statement, and the puzzle is figuring out how it can be true.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have no idea, but have fun with it\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-Slashy\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Chemp","CreatedById":154483,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-05T19:41:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBaseball?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GoSlash27","CreatedById":111526,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-05T22:47:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou got it! I told him it was \u0022base 4 modulo 9\u0022 because I thought it was funny.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is the notation used to record a double play in baseball. Shortstop (#6) throws the ball to 2nd base (#4) who throws the ball to first base (#3) resulting in 2 outs.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBest,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-Slashy\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}